obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36159)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1 31st December, 1981, vide notification No. G.S.R. 677(E), dated 28th December, 1981, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36159&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Brahmaputra Board Act, 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36160)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36160&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Central Government should take under its control the regulation and`
  line `development of the inter-State Brahmaputra river valley to the extent hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36161)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36161&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Brahmaputra Board established under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Brahmaputra Valley" means the inter-State Brahmaputra river valley as demarcated under`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) "Fund" means the Brahmaputra Board Fund constituted under section 19;`
  line
  line `(d) "Master Plan" means the Master Plan for the control of floods, bank erosion and improvement`
  line `of drainage in the Brahmaputra Valley prepared under section 12 and includes, where it is prepared in`
  line `parts, each such part;`
  line
  line `(e) "member" means a member of the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "rules" means rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof`
  line `appointed under article 239 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36162)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment and incorporation of the Brahmaputra Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36162&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall`
  line `be established for the purposes of this Act a Board, to be called the Brahmaputra Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman and a Vice-Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the General Manager of the Board and the Financial Adviser to the Board, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) a member each to represent respectively the Governments of Assam, Meghalaya, Nagaland,`
  line `Manipur and Tripura and the Administrations of Arunachal Pradesh and Mizoram, and the NorthEastern Council constituted under section 3 of the North-Eastern Council Act, 1971 (84 of 1971), to`
  line `be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) a member each to represent respectively the Ministries of the Central Government dealing`
  line `with agriculture, irrigation, finance, power and transport to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) a member each to represent respectively the Central Water Commission, the Central`
  line `Electricity Authority, the Geological Survey of India, the India Meteorological Department, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) If any member, for infirmity or otherwise, is incapable of carrying out his duties or is absent on`
  line `leave otherwise than in circumstances not involving the vacation of his appointment, the Central`
  line `Government may appoint another person to act in his place.`
  line
  line `(5) Any officer of the Central Government, not being a member of the Board, if deputed by that`
  line `Government in this behalf, shall have the right to attend the meetings of the Board and take part in the`
  line `proceedings thereof, but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined`
  line `by regulations, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the`
  line `Board relevant to the purpose for which he has been associated, but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(7) No act or proceeding of the Board shall be invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to any rules made under this Act, the Board may constitute a Standing Committee`
  line `consisting of the General Manager of the Board, Financial Adviser to the Board and three other members`
  line `of the Board.`
  line
  line `(9) The Standing Committee constituted under sub-section (8) shall perform, exercise and discharge`
  line `such of the functions, powers and duties of the Board as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to it by`
  line `the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36163)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36163&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The term of office of the members (other than the ex officio`
  line `members) and other conditions of service of the members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36164)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of Chairman and Vice-Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36164&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman shall, in addition to presiding`
  line `over the meetings of the Board, exercise and discharge such powers and duties of the Board as may be`
  line `delegated to him by the Board and such other powers and duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Vice-Chairman of the Board shall exercise and discharge such of the powers and duties of the`
  line `Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Chairman.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36165)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `General Manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36165&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint the General Manager of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the General Manager shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Board and the Chairman of the Board,`
  line `the General Manager shall be the Chief Executive Authority of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The General Manager shall exercise and discharge such of the powers and duties of the Chairman`
  line `as may be prescribed or, as may be delegated to him by the Chairman, and such other powers and duties`
  line `as may be prescribed by rules or determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36166)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Financial Adviser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36166&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint the Financial Adviser to the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Financial Adviser shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36167)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Chief Engineers, Secretary and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36167&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint--`
  line
  line `(a) two Chief Engineers to assist the General Manager of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may appoint such other officers and employees as it considers necessary for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service of the Chief Engineers, the Secretary and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Board shall be such as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36168)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36168&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf, the Board may from time to`
  line `time constitute such Advisory Committees as may be necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36169)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Limits of the Brahmaputra Valley.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36169&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, demarcate the limits of the`
  line `Brahmaputra Valley for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall perform such of its functions and exercise such of the powers within such areas in`
  line `the Brahmaputra Valley as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any notification in respect of any area under this sub-section, the Central`
  line `Government shall consult the Government of the State within which such area is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36170)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Master Plan for the control of floods, etc., in the Brahmaputra Valley.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36170&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `other provisions of this Act and the rules, the Board shall carry out surveys and investigations in the`
  line `Brahmaputra Valley and prepare a Master Plan for the control of floods and bank erosion and`
  line `improvement of drainage in the Brahmaputra Valley:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may prepare the Master Plan in parts with reference to different areas of the`
  line `Brahmaputra Valley or with reference to different matters relating to such areas and may, as often as it`
  line `considers necessary so to do, revise the Master Plan or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In preparing the Master Plan, the Board shall have regard to the development and utilization of the`
  line `water resources of the Brahmaputra Valley for irrigation, hydro power, navigation and other beneficial`
  line `purposes and shall, as far as possible, indicate in such plan the works and other measures which may be`
  line `undertaken for such development.`
  line
  line `(3) The Master Plan shall be submitted to the Central Government as soon as may be after it has been`
  line `prepared or, as the case may be, revised and the Central Government shall, after consultation with the`
  line `State Governments concerned, approve the same subject to such modifications as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36171)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Other functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36171&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall also--`
  line
  line `(a) prepare detailed reports and estimates in respect of the dams and other projects proposed in`
  line `the Master Plan as approved by the Central Government and indicate in each case the cost attributable`
  line `to different purposes or uses;`
  line
  line `(b) draw up standards and specifications for the construction, operation and maintenance of such`
  line `dams and other projects;`
  line
  line `(c) construct, with the approval of the Central Government, multi-purpose dams and works`
  line `connected therewith proposed in the Master Plan as approved by the Central Government and`
  line `maintain and operate such dams and works;`
  line
  line `(d) prepare, in consultation with the State Governments concerned, a phased programme for the`
  line `construction by the State Governments of all dams and other projects proposed in the Master Plan as`
  line `approved by the Central Government other than those referred to in clause (c);`
  line
  line `(e) perform any other such function which may be prescribed for the proper implementation of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) perform such other functions as are supplemental, incidental or consequential to the functions`
  line `specified in section 12 or in clauses (a) to (d), or prescribed under clause (e), of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (d) of sub-section (1), the Board may, with the prior`
  line `approval of the Central Government, construct any dam or project referred to in that clause if it is`
  line `satisfied, having regard to the cost of construction, and the expertise required for the construction, of any`
  line `such dam or project, that it is expedient so to do.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may maintain and operate any dam or project referred to in sub-section (2) for so long`
  line `as it deems it necessary so to do.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "multi-purpose dam" means a dam which is`
  line `constructed for purposes of flood control and for other purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36172)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Conditions subject to which the Board may perform its functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36172&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The performance by the`
  line `Board of the functions specified in, or prescribed under, sections 12 and 13 shall be subject to the`
  line `following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) no multi-purpose dam referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 13 shall be`
  line `constructed by the Board unless the State Governments concerned make available the land required`
  line `for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(b) no dam or project referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 13 shall be constructed`
  line `by the Board unless the State Governments concerned make available free of cost the land required`
  line `for its execution and also undertake to take over its maintenance on and from the expiry of such`
  line `period after its completion as may be specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) no dam or other works shall be undertaken by the Board unless the State Governments`
  line `concerned agree to provide all such assistance as may be required for the construction , operation and`
  line `maintenance thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) such other conditions (including conditions relating to the sharing by the State Governments`
  line `concerned of the whole or any part of cost of dam or other works constructed by the Board) as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government by general or special order published in the Official Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that before undertaking the construction of any such dam or other works, the Board shall`
  line `apprise the State Governments concerned of the cost of construction of, and the benefits likely to accrue`
  line `from, such dam or other works and the proportion in which the State Governments shall share such cost`
  line `and benefits:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Board and the State Governments are unable to agree in respect of the`
  line `sharing of the cost and benefits of any such dam or other works, the Board shall refer the matter to the`
  line `Central Government for decision and the Central Government shall decide such matter after consulting`
  line `the State Governments and the decision of the Central Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36173)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `General powers of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36173&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules, the Board`
  line `shall have the power to do anything which may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of performing`
  line `its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) publish statistics or other information relating to various aspects of flood control, bank erosion`
  line `and drainage in the Brahmaputra Valley;`
  line
  line `(b) require the State Governments concerned to furnish to it information relating to the measures`
  line `undertaken by them for the control of floods and bank erosion and improvement of drainage in the`
  line `Brahmaputra Valley, topographical, meteorological and hydrological and other related data and such`
  line `other information as the Board may require for the performance of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36174)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Forwarding of, and Consultation with respect to, plans, etc., prepared by the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36174&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall forward copies of the Master Plan, reports, estimates, standards and`
  line `specifications prepared by it to the Central Government and the State Governments concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government and the State Governments concerned may consult the Board with`
  line `regard to any matters connected with, or arising out of, such plan, reports, estimates or standards and`
  line specifications.
  line
  line `(3) If, for any reason, a State Government considers it necessary to execute any project for the control`
  line `of floods and bank erosion and drainage work in the Brahmaputra Valley and such project is not`
  line `envisaged in the Master Plan or such project is intended to be executed by the State Government in a`
  line `manner not in conformity with the Master Plan, the State Government may consult the Board with regard`
  line `to the execution of the project and the Board may make such recommendations as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall be construed as imposing any requirement on`
  line `any State Government to consult the Board with regard to the execution of any works which have become`
  line `urgently necessary by reason of any emergency or other extraordinary circumstances.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36175)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Directions and instructions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36175&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time, issue to the Board such directions and instructions as it may deem necessary for the efficient`
  line `administration of this Act and the Board shall carry out such directions and instructions.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `Central Government may, while granting (whether directly or through the Board and after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in that behalf) any financial assistance, by way of loans or`
  line `grants for the execution by any State Government of any dam or other project referred to in clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13 after obtaining the approval of the State Government in this behalf, direct the`
  line `Board to exercise all such powers as may be necessary for satisfying itself that the works are being`
  line `executed in accordance with the standards and specifications laid down therefor by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36176)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Grants and loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36176&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Board such sums of money as the`
  line `Central Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36177)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Constitution of Brahmaputra Board Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36177&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called`
  line `the Brahmaputra Board Fund and there shall be credited thereto the sums paid to the Board by the Central`
  line `Government or by any State Government and all other sums received by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the salary, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other`
  line `employees of the Board and other administrative expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the expenditure on surveys and investigations undertaken by the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) for meeting the cost of construction, operation and maintenance of projects undertaken by the`
  line Board;
  line
  line `(d) for meeting the other expenses of the Board in the discharge of its functions under this Act ;`
  line and
  line
  line `(e) if any sums are received by the Board under sub-section (2) of section 17, for the payment of`
  line `such sums to the State Governments concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36178)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36178&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be prescribed,`
  line `its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated expenditure, the amount of expenditure`
  line `which any State Government has undertaken to provide for, and forward the same to the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36179)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36179&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be`
  line `prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous year, and forward`
  line `copies thereof to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36180)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36180&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of the Board shall be maintained and audited in such manner`
  line `as may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36181)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disputes between the Board and the State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36181&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any dispute arises between`
  line `the Board and any State Government regarding any matter covered by this Act or touching or arising out`
  line `of it, it shall be referred to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall endeavour to resolve the dispute by negotiations or conciliation in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), if the Central Government considers,`
  line `whether before initiating action for resolving a dispute by negotiations or conciliation or at any stage after`
  line `initiating such action, that the dispute is of such a nature that it is necessary or expedient to refer it to`
  line `arbitration, the Central Government shall , in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, refer`
  line `the matter in dispute to an arbitrator who shall be appointed by the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The arbitrator may appoint two or more persons as assessors to assist him in the proceedings`
  line `before him.`
  line
  line `(5) The decision of the arbitrator shall be final and binding on the parties to the dispute and shall be`
  line `given effect to by them.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940) shall apply to any arbitration under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36182)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Removal, etc., of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36182&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may remove from the Board any`
  line `member who, in its opinion,`
  line
  line `(a) refuses to act,`
  line
  line `(b) has become incapable to act,`
  line
  line `(c) has so abused his office as a member so as to render his continuance on the Board detrimental`
  line `to the interests of the public, or`
  line
  line `(d) is otherwise unsuitable to continue as a member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may suspend any member pending an inquiry against him.`
  line
  line `(3) No order or removal under this section shall be made unless the member concerned has been`
  line `given an opportunity to submit his explanation to the Central Government and when such order is passed,`
  line `the seat of the member removed shall be declared vacant.`
  line
  line `(4) A member who has been removed under this section shall not be eligible for reappointment as a`
  line `member or in any capacity under the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Board fails to carry out its functions or directions issued by the Central Government under`
  line `this Act, the Central Government shall have power to reconstitute the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36183)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to enter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36183&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf, any officer of the Board generally or`
  line `specially authorised by the Board in this behalf, may, at all reasonable times, enter upon any land or`
  line `premises and there do such things as may be reasonably necessary for the purpose of lawfully carrying`
  line `out any of its works or of making any survey, examination or investigation, preliminary or incidental to`
  line `the exercise of powers or the performance of the functions by the Board under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such officer shall enter any building or any enclosed court or garden attached to a`
  line `dwelling house, unless with the consent of the occupier thereof, without previously giving such occupier`
  line `at least seven days' notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36184)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Members, officers and employees of the Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36184&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `All members, officers`
  line `and employees of the Board shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36185)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36185&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against the Government or any officer of the Government or any member, officer or employee of`
  line `the Board for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against the Board for any damage caused, or likely to`
  line `be caused by anything in good faith done or purported to be done under this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations, and in particular, it shall not be the responsibility of the Board to provide for relief measures`
  line `necessitated by floods or by breaches and failures of works.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36186)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36186&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the matters with respect to the standing committee of the Board referred to in sub-section (8)`
  line `and (9) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office of members (other than the ex officio members), and other conditions of`
  line `service of the members, of the Board under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and duties of the Chairman and Vice-Chairman under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms and conditions of service and the powers and duties of the General Manager under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(e) the terms and conditions of service of the Financial Adviser under section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions and restrictions with respect to carrying out surveys and investigations and`
  line `preparation of a Master Plan under sub-section (1) of section 12 and other matters relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(g) the additional functions of the Board under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions and restrictions with respect to the general power of the Board under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15 and other matters relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(i) the form in which, and the time when, the Board shall prepare its budget under section 20 and`
  line `its annual report under section 21, and the manner in which the accounts of the Board shall be`
  line `maintained and audited under section 22;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner in which the Central Government shall endeavour to resolve, under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 23, the disputes referred to therein and the form and manner in which such disputes may be`
  line `referred, under sub-section (3) of that section, to arbitration;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions and restrictions with respect to the exercise of the power to enter under`
  line `section 25 and other matters relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be,`
  line `or may be, made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36187)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36187&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and the`
  line `rules generally to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which, and the purposes for which, the Board may associate with itself any`
  line `person under sub-section (6) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the General Manager of the Board which may be determined under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions of service of the Chief Engineers, the Secretary and other officers`
  line `and employees of the Board under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter in respect of which provision is to be or may be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (36188)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354&sectionId=36188&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_24_32_00004_198046_1517807326354
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
